The IAM Cloud SSO Toolkit is a very handy tool for developers and IT pros, to help remove burden of integrating enterprise-grade Identity & Access Management to any Line-of-Business application. Our Toolkit allows developers and IT Pros to focus instead on their own area of expertise, knowing the IAM is being handled by our technology.
With astonishingly little effort, organizations now can integrate Single Sign-On into their existing range of applications. Our Toolkit can be used for both desktop and web based applications. The Toolkit has powerful yet simple user-friendly interface, meaning programmers can make the most of our technology without being an identity expert.
We have built the SSO Toolkit on top of IAM Cloud’s powerful identity engine, allowing applications to accept users from an enormous range of different sources and repositories, including Active Directory, WorkDay, PeopleSoft, SQL, Oracle and many more.
Authentication is achieved, we then respond with expected attributes directly from our Cloud Vault. Using our Toolkit these can then be consumed within your application exactly like any other dataset.

description:
The WinSCP .NET assembly is a .NET wrapper around WinSCP’s scripting interface that allows your code to connect to a remote machine and manipulate remote files over SFTP, SCP, and FTP sessions.
    
The library is primarily intended for advanced automation tasks that require conditional processing, loops or other control structures for which the basic scripting interface is too limited. The library is not a general purpose file transfer library. It particularly lacks support for interactive processing and as such it is not well suited for use in GUI applications.

For documentation and examples of use, see project website.

The NuGet package includes the assembly itself and a required WinSCP executable. When installed, it adds the assembly as reference to your project and sets up WinSCP executable to be copied to project output directory, so that it can be found on run-time.
summary: The WinSCP .NET assembly is a .NET wrapper around WinSCP’s scripting interface.
